 That install applies to "Smarty and the nasty gluttons" © 2020 Eero xxx
 
 That install requires WHDLoad to be in the path. It can be found in the
 WHDLoad package.

 You need 0.5 MB ChipMem and 0.5 FastMem
 
 You can quit the game by pressing F10 (key can be changed with	Tooltype 
 "QuitKey=").
 
 If you have problems with this installation please try first to get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad's WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also doesn't succeeds inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad's WWW-Page.

 For full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

 version 1.1 (22.10.2024) done by JOTD:
 - adapted for WHDload 19

 version 1.0 (16.08.2020):
 - initial release
 - CUSTOM2 to use second/blue button to jump
 - CUSTOM1 bits to enable trainer:
   * infinite lives
   * one key completes level
   * infinite special items 
 - CUSTOM5 to skip introduction
 - added P key for pause
 - fixed broken map display on fast machines
 - joypad controls: play for pause, rev+fwd+yellow quit to WB
 - quitkey works on 68000 in most parts of the game
 - highscores saved & loaded to/from file (unless you cheat)
 - nice icon by coldacid

not done yet, but planned

 - quit current game (esc)
 - level select: load proper tileset
 - quit in end sequence



